headline: Pepsi to Buy Poppi for Nearly $2 Billion, Broadening Brand Portfolio
summary: PepsiCo  said it is buying the prebiotic soda brand Poppi for nearly $2 billion, sending shares of the food and beverage company 1.6% higher.  The news comes as Pepsi and its rivals have been seeking to expand their product portfolios to drive further growth as economic conditions and changing tastes among consumers weigh on demand.  Inflation has squeezed consumers’ budgets, hurting demand for sodas and snacks.
